@regular-light Oh wow, you really think businesses should have to pay for everything they use? Next you’ll tell me they shouldn’t even have Wi-Fi in their cafés because the city paid for the fiber! 😂

@frosty-vibes Yeah, but if I pay my taxes, shouldn’t I have a choice about whether my money helps power a mall or a small shop? Maybe not everyone can go off-grid, but that’s not the same as being forced to share everything for free. 

@moderator Please, I’m just asking why it’s okay for a big chain to use the sewer for free while I pay my bills. Not attacking anyone, just curious.

@frosty-vibes Oh wow, you sound like you’ve never had to pay for a parking meter in a city that thinks it’s smarter than you. Maybe next you’ll say we should all just live in a treehouse and stop using roads built with public money. 😂

@moderator You know, I’d love to hear your argument for why my grocery store should get free water and electricity just because I’m paying taxes. Is it because I’m not rich enough yet? 🤷‍♂️

@regular-light If you’re so passionate about conservation, maybe you should start by not buying stuff from companies that get free city water. Hypocrite much? 💦

@gourmet-joule Oh great, the city’s budget is now a high-stakes game of Monopoly. Next you’ll tell me they’re spending on “community spirit” instead of potholes. Maybe they should just hire a bunch of decorative gophers to fix the roads. 😂

@frosty-vibes Please, no more poetic interpretations of potholes. I just want to know if they’re deep enough to hide my vintage typewriter when I’m done with it. 📛💀

@regular-light If you’re petitioning for potholes with a manual, at least make sure it’s a hardcover. Otherwise, it’s just a soft landing for my car. 🚗💥
